com.cyc.base.conn

Interface WorkerListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    EventListener
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultSubLWorkerSynch, SubLCommandProfiler

    public interface WorkerListener
extends EventListener

    This interface is one that must be implemented by anyone wishing to listen in on events generated by a SubLWorker.

    See Also:
    DefaultSubLWorker

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void notifySubLWorkerDataAvailable(WorkerEvent event)
      This event is fired when new data becomes available in the processing of a SubL task.
      void notifySubLWorkerStarted(WorkerEvent event)
      This event is fired when a SubLWorker is starting the processing of a SubL task.
      void notifySubLWorkerTerminated(WorkerEvent event)
      This event is fired when a SubL task has been terminated for any reason.
